{"title_page": "Parler", "text_new": "{{short description|Social networking service}}\n{{for|the family name|Parler family}}\n{{Infobox website\n| name = Parler\n| logo = Parler_logo.png\n| logo size = \n| screenshot = \n| caption = Parler logo\n| company_type = [[Public company|Public]]\n| website_type = [[News]], [[social networking service]]\n| language = [[Multilingualism|Multilingual]]\n| traded_as = \n| foundation = 2018\n| location = \n| coordinates = \n| area_served = Worldwide\n| founder = John Matze\n| key_people = \n| industry = [[Internet]]\n| revenue = \n| net_income = \n| operating_income = \n| assets = \n| equity = \n| num_employees = \n| subsid = \n| alexa = \n| registration = Required\n| num_users = \n| launch_date = August 2018\n| current_status = Active\n| programming_language = \n| footnotes = \n| url                    = {{URL|https://parler.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Parler''' is a US-based [[social networking]] service launched in August 2018 and regarded as an alternative to [[Twitter]]. It is marketed as an unbiased, free-speech social media platform focused on protecting users' rights.<ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.dailydot.com/layer8/what-is-parler-free-speech-social-media-app/|title=Parler: Are Conservatives Pivoting to a New Social Media App?|last=Rothschild|first=Mike|date=June 5, 2019|website=The Daily Dot|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=June 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Content==\n\nParler is considered to be among a list of [[alternative media]] social network platforms, including [[Minds]], [[MeWe]], [[Gab]] and [[BitChute]], created in response to alleged anti-conservative bias in mainstream social media platforms such as [[Twitter]], [[YouTube]], [[Instagram]] and [[Facebook]].<ref name=\"Spectator USA 7 May 2019\">{{cite news |title=A complete guide to finding your favorite banned celebrity online |url=https://spectator.us/guide-finding-banned-celebrity-online/ |accessdate=28 May 2019 |work=Spectator USA |date=7 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nIt has been criticized by [[Politico]] for permitting content it deems [[Criticism of Islam|anti-Islamic]] and [[antifeminism|anti-feminist]]. A review of the service in May 2019 described its activity as \"devoted mostly to a small universe of Trump-friendly discussions\". <ref name=\"POLITICO 28 May 2019\">{{cite news |last1=Schreckinger |first1=Ben |title=Amid censorship fears, Trump campaign 'checking out' alternative social network |url=https://www.politico.com/story/2019/05/28/trump-campaign-twitter-1345357 |accessdate=28 May 2019 |work=[[Politico]] |date=28 May 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nParler (from the [[French language|French]] word for \"to speak\") was founded by [[Chief executive officer|CEO]] John Matze in 2018.<ref name=\"POLITICO 28 May 2019\" /><ref name=\":0\">{{cite news|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/maga-social-media-networks-gab-and-parler-are-at-war-with-each-over-a-potential-trump-account|title=MAGA Social Media Networks Are at War With Each Over a Potential Trump Account|last=Sommer|first=Will|date=2019-06-04|work=The Daily Beast|access-date=2019-06-04|language=en}}</ref> Its rollout in August 2018 was plagued by bugs that made it almost unusable initially.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\"Spectator USA 7 May 2019\" />\n\nFrom December 2018 through 2019, the service gained a surge in usership after prominent conservative personalities, among them [[Brad Parscale]], Senator [[Mike Lee (American politician)|Mike Lee]], and activist [[Candace Owens]], signed up and publicized the network to their social media followers on other platforms.<ref name=\"POLITICO 28 May 2019\" /> Matze had met with Parscale in early May 2019 prior to signing up.<ref name=\":0\" /> Other notable users include persons banned from Twitter or other networks, such as [[Anthony Cumia]], [[Jacob Wohl]], [[Laura Loomer]], [[Milo Yiannopoulos]], [[Paul Joseph Watson]] and [[Roger Stone]].<ref name=\"Spectator USA 7 May 2019\" />\n\nAccording to Matze, as of May 2019, Parler had about 100,000 users.<ref name=\"POLITICO 28 May 2019\" /> Parler's user base more than doubled in June 2019 after around 200,000 nationalists from [[Saudi Arabia]] joined the website after allegedly being mass-banned from Twitter.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Cuillford |first1=Elizabeth |last2=Paul |first2=Katie |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-twitter-saudi-politics-idUSKCN1TE32S |title=Unhappy with Twitter, thousands of Saudis join pro-Trump social network Parler |date=14 June 2019 |publisher=Reuters |accessdate=15 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official|https://parler.com}}\n\n[[Category:Internet properties established in 2018]]\n[[Category:American social networking websites]]\n[[Category:Alt-right]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Social networking service}}\n{{for|the family name|Parler family}}\n{{Infobox website\n| name = Parler\n| logo = Parler_logo.png\n| logo size = \n| screenshot = \n| caption = Parler logo\n| company_type = [[Public company|Public]]\n| website_type = [[News]], [[social networking service]]\n| language = [[Multilingualism|Multilingual]]\n| traded_as = \n| foundation = 2018\n| location = \n| coordinates = \n| area_served = Worldwide\n| founder = John Matze\n| key_people = \n| industry = [[Internet]]\n| revenue = \n| net_income = \n| operating_income = \n| assets = \n| equity = \n| num_employees = \n| subsid = \n| alexa = \n| registration = Required\n| num_users = \n| launch_date = August 2018\n| current_status = Active\n| programming_language = \n| footnotes = \n| url                    = {{URL|https://parler.com}}\n}}\n\n'''Parler''' is a US-based [[social networking]] service launched in August 2018 and regarded as an alternative to [[Twitter]]. It is marketed as an unbiased, free-speech social media platform focused on protecting users' rights.<ref name=\":1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.dailydot.com/layer8/what-is-parler-free-speech-social-media-app/|title=Parler: Are Conservatives Pivoting to a New Social Media App?|last=Rothschild|first=Mike|date=June 5, 2019|website=The Daily Dot|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=June 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Content==\n\nParler is considered to be among a list of [[alternative media]] social network platforms, including [[Minds]], [[MeWe]], [[Gab]] and [[BitChute]], created in response to alleged anti-conservative bias in mainstream social media platforms such as [[Twitter]], [[Youtube]], [[Instragram]] and [[Facebook]].<ref name=\"Spectator USA 7 May 2019\">{{cite news |title=A complete guide to finding your favorite banned celebrity online |url=https://spectator.us/guide-finding-banned-celebrity-online/ |accessdate=28 May 2019 |work=Spectator USA |date=7 May 2019}}</ref>\n\nIt has been criticized by [[Politico]] for permitting content it deems [[Criticism of Islam|anti-Islamic]] and [[antifeminism|anti-feminist]]. A review of the service in May 2019 described its activity as \"devoted mostly to a small universe of Trump-friendly discussions\". <ref name=\"POLITICO 28 May 2019\">{{cite news |last1=Schreckinger |first1=Ben |title=Amid censorship fears, Trump campaign 'checking out' alternative social network |url=https://www.politico.com/story/2019/05/28/trump-campaign-twitter-1345357 |accessdate=28 May 2019 |work=[[Politico]] |date=28 May 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nParler (from the [[French language|French]] word for \"to speak\") was founded by [[Chief executive officer|CEO]] John Matze in 2018.<ref name=\"POLITICO 28 May 2019\" /><ref name=\":0\">{{cite news|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/maga-social-media-networks-gab-and-parler-are-at-war-with-each-over-a-potential-trump-account|title=MAGA Social Media Networks Are at War With Each Over a Potential Trump Account|last=Sommer|first=Will|date=2019-06-04|work=The Daily Beast|access-date=2019-06-04|language=en}}</ref> Its rollout in August 2018 was plagued by bugs that made it almost unusable initially.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\"Spectator USA 7 May 2019\" />\n\nFrom December 2018 through 2019, the service gained a surge in usership after prominent conservative personalities, among them [[Brad Parscale]], Senator [[Mike Lee (American politician)|Mike Lee]], and activist [[Candace Owens]], signed up and publicized the network to their social media followers on other platforms.<ref name=\"POLITICO 28 May 2019\" /> Matze had met with Parscale in early May 2019 prior to signing up.<ref name=\":0\" /> Other notable users include persons banned from Twitter or other networks, such as [[Anthony Cumia]], [[Jacob Wohl]], [[Laura Loomer]], [[Milo Yiannopoulos]], [[Paul Joseph Watson]] and [[Roger Stone]].<ref name=\"Spectator USA 7 May 2019\" />\n\nAccording to Matze, as of May 2019, Parler had about 100,000 users.<ref name=\"POLITICO 28 May 2019\" /> Parler's user base more than doubled in June 2019 after around 200,000 nationalists from [[Saudi Arabia]] joined the website after allegedly being mass-banned from Twitter.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Cuillford |first1=Elizabeth |last2=Paul |first2=Katie |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-twitter-saudi-politics-idUSKCN1TE32S |title=Unhappy with Twitter, thousands of Saudis join pro-Trump social network Parler |date=14 June 2019 |publisher=Reuters |accessdate=15 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official|https://parler.com}}\n\n[[Category:Internet properties established in 2018]]\n[[Category:American social networking websites]]\n[[Category:Alt-right]]\n", "name_user": "Mandarax", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fix typo", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parler"}
{"title_page": "Sarah D. Goode", "text_new": "<noinclude><!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=Sarah D. Goode|timestamp=20200410170421|year=2020|month=April|day=10|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=Sarah D. Goode|date=10 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point --></noinclude>\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox academic\n| name               = Sarah D. Goode\n| image              = \n| image_size         = \n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \n| native_name_lang   = \n| birth_name         = <!-- use only if different from full/othernames -->\n| birth_date         = <!-- {{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}}  -->\n| birth_place        = \n| death_date         = <!-- {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| region             = \n| nationality        = British\n| other_names        = \n| occupation         = CEO, writer\n| period             = \n| known_for          = {{Plainlist|\n* ''[[Understanding and Addressing Adult Sexual Attraction to Children]]''\n* ''Paedophiles in Society''}}\n| title              = \n| boards             = <!--board or similar positions extraneous to main occupation-->\n| spouse             = \n| children           = \n| parents            = \n| family             =\n| awards             = <!--notable national level awards only-->\n| website            = \n| education          = \n| alma_mater         = [[University of Warwick]] (MA, PhD)\n| thesis_title       = \n| thesis_url         = \n| thesis_year        = \n| school_tradition   = \n| doctoral_advisor   = \n| influences         = \n| era                = \n| discipline         = [[Sociology]]\n| sub_discipline     = <!--academic discipline specialist area \u2013 e.g. Sub-atomic research, 20th Century Danish specialist, Pauline research, Arcadian and Ugaritic specialist-->\n| workplaces         = [[StopSO (Specialist Treatment Organisation for the Prevention of Sexual Offending)]]\n| doctoral_students  = \n| notable_students   = <!--only those with WP articles-->\n| main_interests     = \n| notable_works      = \n| notable_ideas      = \n| influenced         = <!--must be referenced from a third party source-->\n| signature          = \n| signature_alt      = \n| signature_size     = \n| footnotes          = \n}}\n\n'''Sarah D. Goode''' is a British [[sociologist]], writer, [[CEO]] of StopSO, and former Honorary Researcher and Coordinator of the Center for Research and Policy for the Study of Community Welfare at the [[University of Winchester]], UK.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/author/dr-sarah-d-goode/ | title = Dr Sarah D Goode | access-date = 13 October 2017 | website= Huffpost}}</ref> She is the author of books including \"Understanding and addressing adult sexual attraction to children\" and \"Paedophiles in Society\", in which she analyses the situation of [[paedophilia]] in contemporary Western society.<ref>{{cite book |last=Goode |first=Sarah |year=2010 |access-date=13 October 2017 |title=Understanding and Addressing Adult Sexual Attraction to Children |url=https://books.google.com/?id=pKcQY5fUfFAC |location= London|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-0-203-87374-8 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://us.macmillan.com/author/sarahdgoode |title=Sarah D. Goode Palgrave-MacMillan |accessdate=2017-10-13 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130924030553/http://us.macmillan.com/author/sarahdgoode |archivedate=24 September 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==Education and work==\nShe trained as a paediatric occupational therapist, going on to study an MA in Sociological Research in Healthcare at the University of Warwick before studying for a PhD in Sociology.<ref name=psychotherapyUK>{{cite web | url = https://www.psychotherapyuk.co.uk/dr-sarah-goode/ | title = Dr Sarah Goode | access-date = 13 October 2017 | website= psychotherapyUK}}</ref>\n\nShe worked as a lecturer at the Warwick Medical School and was a senior lecturer at the University of Winchester, leading the Research and Policy Centre for the Study of Wellbeing in Communities.<ref name=psychotherapyUK/>\n\nHer work was featured in a [[Channel Four]] documentary, and she has appeared in interviews on [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] and the [[BBC]].<ref name=psychotherapyUK/><ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/health-and-families/i-am-a-paedophile-is-our-approach-to-sex-offenders-helping-to-create-more-victims-9880699.html | title = 'I am a paedophile': Is our approach to sex offenders helping to create more victims? |author=Steve Humphries |date=24 November 2014|access-date = 11 April 2020 | website= The Independent}}</ref>\n\nShe has praised the work of the [[Prevention Project Dunkelfeld]] and the [[Lucy Faithfull, Baroness Faithfull|Lucy Faithfull Foundation]].<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/dr-sarah-d-goode/chemical-castration-paedophiles_b_9658586.html | title = Chemical Castration - or Compassion for Paedophiles? |author=Sarah Goode |date=12 April 2016|access-date = 11 April 2020 | website= Huffpost}}</ref> Whilst being critical of practices such as [[chemical castration]] and critical of current clinical [[psychiatric]] criteria, believing them to be too narrow.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Rickard |first1=Diana |date=September 2013 |title=Reviewed Work: Paedophiles in Society: Reflecting on Sexuality, Abuse and Hope by Sarah D. Goode |journal=Contemporary Sociology |volume=42 |issue=5 |pages=745\u2013747 |doi= 10.1177/0094306113499713f|jstor=23524433 }}</ref>\n\n===Understanding and addressing adult sexual attraction to children===\nIn her book ''Understanding and addressing adult sexual attraction to children'', presents case studies based on interviews she conducted with [[pedophiles]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Smith|first1=Clarissa|date=November 2010 |title=Review: Sarah D. Goode, Understanding and Addressing Sexual Attraction to Children: A Study of Paedophiles in Contemporary Society |url=https://www.participations.org/Volume%207/Issue%202/PDF/smith.pdf |journal=Participation: Journal of Audience and Reception Studies |volume=7 |issue=2 |pages=396\u2013398 |doi= |access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Terry|first1=Karen|date=1 December 2011 |title=Book Review: Understanding and Addressing Adult Sexual Attraction to Children: A Study of Paedophiles in Contemporary Society |doi=10.1177/0361684311410542 |journal=Psychology of Women Quarterly}}</ref> She uses these case studies, as well as previous studies to counteract some of the false beliefs and alarmism that developed in the late 1970s in the United States, and in the early 1980s in Europe.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Plummer|first1=Ken|date=November 2010 |title=Understanding and addressing adult sexual attraction to children: a study of paedophiles in contemporary society |journal=International Journal of Research & Method in Education |volume=33 |issue=3 |pages=318\u2013319 |doi=10.1080/1743727X.2010.512100 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Bellamy|first1=Clifford|date=30 September 2010 |title=Book Reviews: Understanding and addressing adult sexual attraction to children|journal=Journal of Sexual Aggression |volume=16 |issue=3 |pages=373\u2013376 |doi=10.1080/13552600.2010.504602|access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Works==\n* {{citation|author=Sarah D. Goode|title= Understanding and addressing adult sexual attraction to children: a study of paedophiles in contemporary society| publisher=Routledge|place=London/New York|year=2010|isbn= 9780415446266 |lang=en|ref=none}}\n* {{citation|author=Sarah D. Goode|title= Paedophiles in society: reflecting on sexuality, abuse and hope| publisher=Palgrave Macmillan|place=Basingstoke|year=2011|isbn= 9780230271883|lang=en|ref=none}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Goode, Sarah D}}\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Warwick]]\n[[Category:British sociologists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Women sociologists]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n\n\n{{UK-sociologist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "<noinclude><!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=Sarah D. Goode|timestamp=20200410170421|year=2020|month=April|day=10|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=Sarah D. Goode|date=10 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point --></noinclude>\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}}\n{{Use British English|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox academic\n| name               = Sarah D. Goode\n| image              = \n| image_size         = \n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| native_name        = \n| native_name_lang   = \n| birth_name         = <!-- use only if different from full/othernames -->\n| birth_date         = <!-- {{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}}  -->\n| birth_place        = \n| death_date         = <!-- {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| region             = \n| nationality        = British\n| other_names        = \n| occupation         = CEO, writer\n| period             = \n| known_for          = {{Plainlist|\n* ''[[Understanding and Addressing Adult Sexual Attraction to Children]]''\n* ''Paedophiles in Society''}}\n| title              = \n| boards             = <!--board or similar positions extraneous to main occupation-->\n| spouse             = \n| children           = \n| parents            = \n| family             =\n| awards             = <!--notable national level awards only-->\n| website            = \n| education          = \n| alma_mater         = [[University of Warwick]] (MA, PhD)\n| thesis_title       = \n| thesis_url         = \n| thesis_year        = \n| school_tradition   = \n| doctoral_advisor   = \n| influences         = \n| era                = \n| discipline         = [[Sociology]]\n| sub_discipline     = <!--academic discipline specialist area \u2013 e.g. Sub-atomic research, 20th Century Danish specialist, Pauline research, Arcadian and Ugaritic specialist-->\n| workplaces         = [[StopSO (Specialist Treatment Organisation for the Prevention of Sexual Offending)]]\n| doctoral_students  = \n| notable_students   = <!--only those with WP articles-->\n| main_interests     = \n| notable_works      = \n| notable_ideas      = \n| influenced         = <!--must be referenced from a third party source-->\n| signature          = \n| signature_alt      = \n| signature_size     = \n| footnotes          = \n}}\n\n'''Sarah D. Goode''' is a British [[sociologist]], writer, [[CEO]] of StopSO, and former Honorary Researcher and Coordinator of the Center for Research and Policy for the Study of Community Welfare at the [[University of Winchester]], UK.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/author/dr-sarah-d-goode/ | title = Dr Sarah D Goode | access-date = 13 October 2017 | website= Huffpost}}</ref> She is the author of books including \"Understanding and addressing adult sexual attraction to children\" and \"Paedophiles in Society\", in which she analyses the situation of [[paedophilia]] in contemporary Western society.<ref>{{cite book |last=Goode |first=Sarah |year=2010 |access-date=13 October 2017 |title=Understanding and Addressing Adult Sexual Attraction to Children |url=https://books.google.com/?id=pKcQY5fUfFAC |location= London|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-0-203-87374-8 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://us.macmillan.com/author/sarahdgoode |title=Sarah D. Goode Palgrave-MacMillan |accessdate=2017-10-13 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130924030553/http://us.macmillan.com/author/sarahdgoode |archivedate=24 September 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n==Education and work==\nShe trained as a paediatric occupational therapist, going on to study an MA in Sociological Research in Healthcare at the University of Warwick before studying for a PhD in Sociology.<ref name=psychotherapyUK>{{cite web | url = https://www.psychotherapyuk.co.uk/dr-sarah-goode/ | title = Dr Sarah Goode | access-date = 13 October 2017 | website= psychotherapyUK}}</ref>\n\nShe worked as a lecturer at the Warwick Medical School and was a senior lecturer at the University of Winchester, leading the Research and Policy Centre for the Study of Wellbeing in Communities.<ref name=psychotherapyUK/>\n\nHer work was featured in a [[Channel Four]] documentary, and she has appeared in interviews on [[ITV (TV network)|ITV]] and the [[BBC]].<ref name=psychotherapyUK/><ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/health-and-families/i-am-a-paedophile-is-our-approach-to-sex-offenders-helping-to-create-more-victims-9880699.html | title = 'I am a paedophile': Is our approach to sex offenders helping to create more victims? |author=Steve Humphries |date=24 November 2014|access-date = 11 April 2020 | website= The Independent}}</ref>\n\nShe has praised the work of the [[Prevention Project Dunkelfeld]] and the [[Lucy Faithfull, Baroness Faithfull|Lucy Faithfull Foundation]].<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/dr-sarah-d-goode/chemical-castration-paedophiles_b_9658586.html | title = Chemical Castration - or Compassion for Paedophiles? |author=Sarah Goode |date=12 April 2016|access-date = 11 April 2020 | website= Huffpost}}</ref> Whilst being critical of practices such as [[chemical castration]] and critical of current clinical [[psychiatric]] criteria, believing them to be too narrow.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Rickard |first1=Diana |date=September 2013 |title=Reviewed Work: Paedophiles in Society: Reflecting on Sexuality, Abuse and Hope by Sarah D. Goode |journal=Contemporary Sociology |volume=42 |issue=5 |pages=745\u2013747 |doi= 10.1177/0094306113499713f|jstor=23524433 }}</ref>\n\n===Understanding and addressing adult sexual attraction to children===\nIn her book ''Understanding and addressing adult sexual attraction to children'', presents case studies based on interviews she conducted with [[pedophiles]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Smith|first1=Clarissa|date=November 2010 |title=Review: Sarah D. Goode, Understanding and Addressing Sexual Attraction to Children: A Study of Paedophiles in Contemporary Society |url=https://www.participations.org/Volume%207/Issue%202/PDF/smith.pdf |journal=Participation: Journal of Audience and Reception Studies |volume=7 |issue=2 |pages=396\u2013398 |doi= |access-date=11 April 2020}}</ref> She uses these case studies, as well as previous studies to counteract some of the false beliefs and alarmism that developed in the late 1970s in the United States, and in the early 1980s in Europe.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Plummer|first1=Ken|date=November 2010 |title=Understanding and addressing adult sexual attraction to children: a study of paedophiles in contemporary society |journal=International Journal of Research & Method in Education |volume=33 |issue=3 |pages=318\u2013319 |doi=10.1080/1743727X.2010.512100 }}</ref>\n\n==Works==\n* {{citation|author=Sarah D. Goode|title= Understanding and addressing adult sexual attraction to children: a study of paedophiles in contemporary society| publisher=Routledge|place=London/New York|year=2010|isbn= 9780415446266 |lang=en|ref=none}}\n* {{citation|author=Sarah D. Goode|title= Paedophiles in society: reflecting on sexuality, abuse and hope| publisher=Palgrave Macmillan|place=Basingstoke|year=2011|isbn= 9780230271883|lang=en|ref=none}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{a